	   <tr><td colspan=2>Empress Wyrmbane-Infection: <br><br>There seems to be a misunderstanding regarding my alliance with the High Elf Icewind Novastorm. My pledge of support relates solely to the apprehending and punishment of the Elven betrayers of Tunare. I have no knowledge, nor interest, in any so-called &quot;plots&quot; he may have regarding the sovereignship of yourself and your consort over the lands of Kunark and Grobb. <br><br>Rule as you see fit, it is of no concern to me. <br><br>Bejaizen, of the Clan Izrhume <br>Peacekeeper of the Tranquil <br><br>--- <br><br>&quot;You realize, of course, that they claim far more than Grobb and Kunark as theirs,&quot; Arjaizen warned. <br><br>&quot;Yes. I hope for nothing more than a blunting of her anger. Perhaps she will see it as sufficiently conciliatory that she will turn her attentions elsewhere,&quot; Bejaizen mused. <br><br>&quot;There has been a council called of representatives of all the good-aligned factions. Lord Bulrious has designated that I should attend to speak for the Peacekeepers. We are hopeful to find a solution to the problem of the Trollen/Iksarian alliance.&quot; <br><br>Arjaizen nodded gravely. &quot;Perhaps a resolution can be found, but prepare for the worst.&quot; <br><br>---<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Arjaizen Izrhume<br>21st Circle Wizard of Erudin<br>Centurion Politico, 7th Legion</td></tr>
