<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=10068123291103></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10068123291103><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=93845&mid=10068123291103>RE: Well Met Friend!</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=93845&mid=10068123291103#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=93845><span id=Scholar>Arjaizen</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>65 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Nov 26th 5:05 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.60]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have been reading them.  There are some very good writers here.  While a good number of folk seem to prefer the first person style of writing (what one might call a "true" journal,) in general, I tend to prefer third person.  That's why you see this journal listed as "fiction" rather than "role playing".<br><br>The first chapters of "In the Gorge" were written a while ago.  I've not done a lot to finish the story, but I do plan to. One day, I decided to put the whole thing into a Word document, and I was shocked to learn it was ten pages long.  I wasn't intending to write an "epic" when I started. :-) Now I'm faced with coming up with a suitable climactic finish.<br><br>A note about a couple of the "guest" characters in my stories.  If you are ever on the Nameless server, are a fan of RP, and get the chance to group with Marchant Braemar, do so.  His "owner" is an excellent role-player, and Marchant is a paladin's paladin.  One of my most enjoyable gaming sessions was the night that he and I happened to hook up in the Gorge of King Xorbb, and writing the dramtization of that session is what started my chronicling of Barrik's adventures in the Gorge.  Marchant will appear in the next chapter of the story.<br><br>Barrik ran into Cona in North Karana one night, and we decided to team up.  We fought well together, and decided to play on a regular basis.  Arjaizen has since replaced Barrik, and the Shaman/Wizard pairing has worked even better.  Both are now 21st level, and visiting Castle Mistmoore... well, the front yard of it, anyway. :-)  Cona is also a terrific guy, and a lot of fun to play with.  Not a dyed-in-the-wool role-player, but has a style all his own.<br><br>While I consider Arjaizen as my "main" character, Barrik is actually my highest in levels.  I went on a tear with him for about 7 or 8 levels, rushing to get him to 20th, and his surname.  I also use him as my "scout".  I send him into new zones to get a feel for the place before Arjaizen gets his robes singed.  If I do something stupid with Barrik, I know he's got a chance of getting out with his skin. :-)<br><br>I've played for about a year and a half, but generally only 2 or three times a week.  I also have 5 different characters because I can't make up my mind.  :-) Right now, the one getting a chunk of game time has been Arjaizen's "son" Bejaizen, a paladin of Quellious.  Don't be surprised to see a story or two about him soon.<br><br>Anyway, I'm glad you like the stories so far.  Thank you for the kind and encouraging words.<br><br>Fare well, and good hunting to you!<br>&nbsp;<br>Arjaizen Izrhume<br>21st Circle Wizard of Erudin<br>Centurion Politico, 7th Legion</td></tr>
