<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100586093578069></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100586093578069><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=93845&mid=100586093578069>Climbing the Ladder</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=93845&mid=100586093578069#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=93845><span id=Scholar>Arjaizen</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>65 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Nov 15th 4:48 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>At the High Keep Inn, Barrik answered the knock at the door, to find a comely young girl standing there.  The innkeeper&#8217;s daughter, he guessed.  &#8220;Good morning,&#8221; he said with a smile.<br><br>&#8220;Good morning, Mr. Moonhunter,&#8221; she replied.  &#8220;You wanted us to make sure you were up by 8?&#8221;<br><br>&#8220;Yes, thank you,&#8221; he answered. &#8220;Excuse me," he said as he turned his head back into his room and called out loudly,   &#8220;Cona, get your Barbarian butt out of bed! We're wasting daylight!"<br><br>The girl heard grumbling and muffled groaning, as though a pillow covered the speaker&#8217;s head.  She couldn&#8217;t make out the words.  Barrik had no such problem.<br><br>"Well, maybe if you hadn't had those last half-dozen Halas Heaters, your head wouldn't hurt quite so much."<br><br>The moaning continued, much to the ranger&#8217;s amusement.<br><br>"It is NOT a religious requirement. You clear your head, I'm going to check the mail."<br><br>Giving a silver piece to the innkeeper&#8217;s daughter, Barrik walked down to the High Keep courtyard to see if the fellow from the League of Antonican Bards had any news from his nephews.<br><br>"Good day to you, Mr. Moonhunter," said the young bard at the post. <br><br>&#8220;Well met, lad,&#8221; Barrik responded.  &#8220;What news?&#8221;<br><br>"Something came in for you last night." The bard shuffled through his bag, and pulled out an envelope, containing the seal of Fortenbras Oberonis, Caesar of the 7th Legion. "It looks pretty official."<br><br>With a slight amount of trepidation, Barrik opened the envelope. "Reassigned already? But I just -got- here," he grumbled. "Ah well, " he sighed, "after honor, comes duty. Might as well see where I'm headed next. Though Cona's going to be madder than a wet Kerran at having to move so soon."<br><br>He unfolded the parchment and began to read...<br><br>============<br><br>Hail, Legionnaire! The council of the 7th sends its greetings and congratulations on attaining your 20th season. <br><br>Your efforts in battling the undead hordes in the Desert of Ro and the Marr Oasis have not gone unnoticed. Your service to the 7th has been exemplary. For such service, we are pleased to inform you that effective immediately, you have been promoted to the rank of Legionary.<br><br>Bring pride to the Legion, Barrik Moonhunter!<br><br>To the Glory of the 7th!<br><br>Fortenbras Oberonis, Caesar<br><br>============<br><br>Barrik folded the paper, grin on his face. He made his way back to the Inn. "Just what Cona needs, another reason to hoist a flagon or twelve.  Ah well, at least this time it's a good one, unlike last night&#8217;s so-called holiday.  &#8216;Feast of the Wanton Wenches,&#8217; my foot&#8230;"<br> <br><br>&nbsp;<br>Arjaizen Izrhume<br>21st Circle Wizard of Erudin<br>Centurion Politico, 7th Legion</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
