<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100583973071518></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100583973071518><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=93845&mid=100583973071518>Tales of the 7th</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=93845&mid=100583973071518#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=93845><span id=Scholar>Arjaizen</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>65 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Nov 15th 10:55 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I've written a few stories in the past that centered on my characters in the 7th Legion on the Nameless server.  They got pretty good reviews on the 7th's Web page, so I thought I might see how they do in wider circulation.<br><br>"My" Cast of Characters:<br><br>Arjaizen Izrhume, Wizard of Erudin.  My "first born" and primary character.  Thought to be quite insane by some of his race.  Outgoing, affable, and a jokester.  Loves drinking with his Barbarian friends.  Like I said, insane.<br><br>Barrik Moonhunter, Ranger of Surefall.  My highest level character.  Perhaps he should be thought of as a co-primary.  Firm believer in honor and duty.<br><br>Gilgazin, Cleric of Kaladim.  Rough around the edges, but with a heart of gold.<br><br>Scei, Warrior of Halas.  Originally my RL daughter's character, I took her over when I got my daughter her own account. (Didn't have the heart to delete her.)  More guts than a disemboweled hill giant, will dismiss brutal injury as "just a scratch,"<br><br>Bejaizen, Paladin of Erudin.  The son of Arjaizen. Respects his father, but is often embarassed by him.  Much more of a traditional Erudite than his father.<br><br>My RL daughter also plays, and has a couple of characters I might include from time to time.  They are:<br><br>Euara, Wizard of Erudin.  Daughter of Arjaizen, sister to Bejaizen<br><br>Shaye, Warrior of Halas.  Sister (more like "clone",) of Scei.  This is who she created first when she got her own account.  I gave all Scei's items to her, so getting Shaye to where Scei was wouldn't be quite so painful.  Hey, my kid earned it the first time around. :-)<br><br>All of these characters are members in the 7th Legion.  I hope you enjoy the chronicles of their adventures.<br><br>-Arj<br>&nbsp;<br>Arjaizen Izrhume<br>21st Circle Wizard of Erudin<br>Centurion Politico, 7th Legion</td></tr>
